abstract: Mr. Bloomberg is expected to file paperwork this week in at least one state with an early deadline, although an adviser said the former New York mayor had not made a final decision to run.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg is expected to file paperwork this week in at least one state with an early deadline, although an adviser said the former New York mayor had not made a final decision to run.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg is actively preparing to enter the Democratic presidential primary and is expected to file paperwork this week designating himself as a candidate in at least one state with an early filing deadline, people briefed on Mr. Bloomberg’s plans said.

abstract: Beijing is reining in small financial institutions that once lent with abandon. But the process has generated painful headlines.
snippet: Beijing is reining in small financial institutions that once lent with abandon. But the process has generated painful headlines.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — One bank failed. A second and third were bailed out. Worried depositors of two more banks then rushed to pull out their savings for fear of losing them in a spectacular failure.

abstract: Highlights from yesterday’s DealBook conference, which featured some of the biggest newsmakers in business and policy.
snippet: Highlights from yesterday’s DealBook conference, which featured some of the biggest newsmakers in business and policy.
lead_paragraph: Good Thursday. We held our annual DealBook “Playing for the Long Term” conference yesterday, featuring some of the biggest newsmakers in business and policy. Thanks to everyone who attended. Here’s what stood out to NYT reporters at the event, along with our regular Speed Read news roundup. (Was this email forwarded to you? Sign up here.)

abstract: The new mixed-use mega-project on the Lower East Side heals a civic wound with hundreds of affordable apartments, community perks and a sleek home for Essex Market.
snippet: The new mixed-use mega-project on the Lower East Side heals a civic wound with hundreds of affordable apartments, community perks and a sleek home for Essex Market.
lead_paragraph: Even half-done, Essex Crossing, on the Lower East Side, is shaping up as one of New York’s most promising new mixed-use developments — the anti-Hudson Yards.

headline_main: Essex Crossing Is the Anti-Hudson Yards

abstract: She cycled away from her Boston home and into stardom, leaving a husband and three small children for a journey that came to symbolize women’s independence.
snippet: She cycled away from her Boston home and into stardom, leaving a husband and three small children for a journey that came to symbolize women’s independence.
lead_paragraph: This article is part of Overlooked, a series of obituaries about remarkable people whose deaths, beginning in 1851, went unreported in The Times.

headline_main: Tucson Rejects Sanctuary Status as Places Across U.S. Vote on Their Futures
headline_print_headline: Voters in Tucson Reject Plan to Make Their City  Sanctuary for Migrants
byline_original: By Jacey Fortin and Emily S. Rueb

abstract: In Virginia, Pennsylvania and Kentucky, many voters in historically Republican suburbs supported Democratic candidates, in part because of antipathy toward President Trump.
snippet: In Virginia, Pennsylvania and Kentucky, many voters in historically Republican suburbs supported Democratic candidates, in part because of antipathy toward President Trump.
lead_paragraph: RICHMOND, Va. — For the second Election Day in as many years, suburban voters demonstrated enormous political power in electing or aiding Democratic candidates in historically Republican areas, underscoring the drift of many moderate voters from the G.O.P. in the era of President Trump.

abstract: The administration’s policy would have protected doctors and others who refused to perform procedures on religious grounds.
snippet: The administration’s policy would have protected doctors and others who refused to perform procedures on religious grounds.
lead_paragraph: A federal judge on Wednesday voided the Trump administration’s “conscience rule,” which would have made it easier for health care workers to avoid assisting with abortion or other medical procedures on religious or moral grounds.
